article_title: Florida's health coverage gap leaves Bay County uninsured with few options

article_metadata.description: About 800,000 Floridians fall into the “coverage gap,” the consequence of a crack in the Affordable Care Act (ACA) created by a 2012 Supreme Court ruling. The gap is a health care no-man’s land for some Bay County residents.
article_metadata.author: KATIE LANDECK
